subSubSection.paragraph:
Description.
Body elongate, wide (
Figs. 2E
), with several elongate, dorso-lateral cerata. Cerata arranged in densely packed rows, running from behind oral tentacles to posterior end of body (
Figs. 2E
, 
15B, 15D
). Cerata increase in size in each row, lateral cerata typically shorter, dorsal cerata longer. Oral tentacles elongate and wide (
Figs. 15A, 15C
). Foot corners tentacular, very small (
Figs. 15A, 15C
). Rhinophores elongate, smooth (15B, 15D). Reproductive opening on right anterior portion of body (
Fig. 15B, 15D
). Anal opening lateral, posterior to pericardium (
Fig. 15B, 15D
). Body color cream-white, semi translucent, with viscera visible through skin as a palepinkish mass (
Fig. 2
F–G). Oral tentacles same color as body, with pink-orange bases, rhinophores pink-orange. Cerata translucent white, with cream digestive branches and opaque white cnidosacs.

Digestive system with large, muscular buccal bulb (
Fig. 16A
). Esophagus narrow, short, connecting anteriorly into buccal bulb. Digestive gland with lateral branches entering cerata. Intestine emerging dorsally from left side of digestive gland, forming a loop towards right ventral side of body and running posteriorly to open into anus.

Radular formula 25 × 0.1.0 in 
paratype
(SIO-BIC 
M12412
). Radular teeth narrow (
Fig. 17A
), with arch-shaped base and single central, elongate, sharp cusp. Each tooth with 3 elongate denticles on each side of cusp (
Fig. 17B
). Jaws elongate (
Fig. 17C
), masticatory border with a row of denticles bearing a series of tubercles (
Fig. 17D
).

Reproductive system with very short, oval ampulla (
Fig. 16B
), opening into female gland complex next to prostate opening. Prostate tubular, short, forming two loops, expanding into oval, muscular deferent duct. Penis simple, elongate. No vagina nor bursa copulatrix were observed, probably due to the small size of the specimen dissected.
